# Ground Rules

These define what group members expect from one another and what norms they agree on relating to behaviours and actions. Below are examples of the types of areas it is important to address and examples of what form they might take. 

| Area | Principles & Norms *All members of the group agree to:*  |
| :---- | :---- |
| **Communication** | Discord whenever necessary Sub-24hr response time   |
| **Meetings** | Held online or in person depending on everybody’s schedule   |
| **Deadlines** | Finish work ASAP Communicate timelines when scheduling conflicts occur   |

| Care Statement Outline here how the team will strive to care for the health of each other and the team as a whole during the project duration: |
| :---- |
| Always assume positive intent Build your trust battery with teammates Give constructive feedback  |

| Group RolesSee also the [Guide to Group Roles & Maximizing Performance](https://learningcommons.yorku.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Guide-Group-Roles.pdf)  |  |  |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Group Member** | **Group Role** | **Scope of Role** |
| **Mikail Karimi-Shahidi** | Leader/FacilitatorNotekeeper / Timekeeper | Responsibilities include setting meeting goals, ensuring group members understand concepts, keeping discussions on track, and ensuring tasks are completed on time. Other responsibilities include summarizing meetings and note-taking sessions, presenting group material, and keeping track of time during meetings. |
| **Matthew Bodenstein** | Arbitrator/Monitor | Maintaining a positive group environment and monitoring group dynamics while addressing conflicts, encouraging participation, and providing praise to motivate members. |
| **Harib Shahbaz** | Checker/Editor | Ensuring all pieces of a deliverable are reviewed and completed. compiles contributions from different team members, ensures all sources are adequate cited and reviewed, and engaging in copy editing to ensure the group is ready to submit a deliverable is submitted on time |

| :---- |
|  We will address non-performance by doing the following: Providing an initial reminder to the group member  If non-performance persists we will schedule a formal meeting to address any concerns If there are any conflicts, we will be resolving them through open discussion  If a non-performance continues despite the above, we will escalate the situation to the professor  |
